# Architecture Overview

The lab architecture starts with `{{ app.name }}` running in namespace `{{ app.namespace }}` and expands through progressive DevSecOps readiness layers.

## Logical layers

- Application: image `{{ app.image }}` with `{{ app.replicas }}` requested replica(s).
- Kubernetes raw: base manifests for namespace, workload, service, optional config, placeholder sensitive configuration, and autoscaling.
- Helm: local chart packaging for reusable manifest rendering.
- Ingress: optional HTTP routing and TLS readiness.
- Linkerd: optional service mesh metadata readiness.
- NetworkPolicy: optional ingress-only network isolation readiness.
- Kyverno: optional policy visibility readiness.
- CI: GitHub Actions workflow examples for quality and image security preparation.
- GitOps: ArgoCD Application readiness for Helm-based delivery review.
- Observability: Prometheus ServiceMonitor and Grafana dashboard model.
- Logging: Loki LogQL examples, collector notes, and dashboard model.
- Tracing: OpenTelemetry, OTLP, Tempo, TraceQL, and dashboard model.
- Terraform: local Infrastructure as Code examples.
- Ansible: local automation examples.
- Security Audit: v0.16.0 Security Audit readiness dossier for hardening review.

This architecture overview is descriptive. It does not modify or validate a live platform.
